HEADWORD: Tula metal
<hw>Tu"la met`al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>An alloy of silver, copper, and
lead made at <ets>Tula</ets> in Russia.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>toola metal</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

